   <title>Randel's Global Gridded Spectral Height and Temperature Fields</title>
   <summary>
      <p>This dataset contains once-daily global gridded geopotential
              height and temperature at levels from 1000 millibars up to 1 millibar for the
              period from April 1979 to May 1994.  Bill Randel of NCAR
              interpolated bad and missing data in the grids of <a href="http://rda.ucar.edu/datasets/ds067.1/">ds067.1</a> and
              stored the new data as zonal Fourier coefficients on an
              approximate 4.5 degree latitude/longitude grid (consistent with
              R15 spectral resolution).  Further information can be found in
              NCAR Technical Note 366, which is available from the UCAR
              publications office at (303) 497-8601.</p>
   </summary>
